The Gurujada Foundation of USA has selected SRR Government Arts and Science College vice-principal Kaluvakunta Ramakrishna for the prestigious international Acharya Ratna Spoorthi Award-2015 for his service in Telugu Literature and culture.The award would be presented to Ramakrishna at a function on January 10 at Gurujadaâ€™s native place in Vizianagaram. The award carries a medal, citation and cash prize of Rs. 5,000. Mr. Ramakrishna had earlier received National best NSS programme officer award from President in the year 2014.